description.p:
In embodiments of the present invention, the motor controller comprises:
at least one analog-to-digital-convertor for digitizing the position feedback signals;
at least one pulse width modulation module for generating at least one pulse width modulated signal as at least one of the first and second power signals;
a processing unit provided with an algorithm for determining a duty cycle of the at least one pulse width modulation module for driving the plurality of DC-motors at a plurality of predefined positions.

claim.claim-text:
A motor control system (4) for controlling a plurality (N) of DC-motors (1), the motor control system (4) comprising:
- a motor controller (10), adapted for providing a number (N) of first power signals (Us) each for being applied to one of the DC motors (1) and a single common second power signal (Ts) for powering the plurality (N) of DC-motors (1), and adapted for receiving a plurality (N) of position feedback signals (Ps) from the plurality of DC-motors;
- one or more motor modules (2) connectable to the plurality (N) of DC-motors (1) and comprising for each of the plurality of DC-motors (1) a variable impedance (3) adapted for being operatively connected to one of the DC motors (1) and for creating an impedance (R1, R2) indicative of a position of said one DC-motor (1);
- a wire interface (13) for interconnecting the one or more motor modules (2) and the motor controller (10) for transferring the plurality (N) of first power signals (Us) and the single common second power signal (Ts) and the plurality (N) of position feedback signals (Ps); wherein each variable impedance (3) is arranged for being powered by one of the first power signals (Us) and by the common second power signal (Ts) and for generating one of the position feedback signals (Ps) when the corresponding DC-motor (1) is being powered;

and wherein the number of wires of the wire interface (13) is twice the number (N) of DC-motors plus one.

The motor control system (4) according to any of the previous claims, wherein the motor controller (10) comprises:
- at least one analog-to-digital-convertor (ADC1) for digitizing the position feedback signals (Ps);
- at least one pulse width modulation module (PWM1) for generating at least one pulse width modulated signal as at least one of the first and second power signals (Us, Ts);
- a processing unit (CPU) provided with an algorithm for determining a duty cycle of the at least one pulse width modulation module (PWM1) for driving the plurality of DC-motors (1) at a plurality of predefined positions.

Method for driving a plurality (N) of DC-motors (1) over a wire interface selectively in a first and second direction, whereby the number of wires of the wire-interface (13) is twice the number (N) of DC-motors plus one, and for reading the positions of the plurality (N) of DC-motors (1), the method comprising the steps of:
a) generating a plurality (N) of first power signals (Us), generating a single common second power signal (Ts), and applying the plurality (N) of first power signals (Us) and the single common second power signal (Ts) to the plurality (N) of DC-motors (1) over the wire interface (13), whereby at least one of the first power signals (Us) and the single common second power signal (Ts) have different voltage levels for driving at least one of the DC-motors (1);
b) generating at last one position feedback signal (Ps) of said at least one driven DC-motor (1), and applying the at least one position feedback signal (Ps) to the wire interface (13);
c) determining at least one actual position of the at least one driven DC-motor (1) based on the at least one position feedback signal (Ps);
d) adjusting the plurality (N) of first power signals (Us) and the single common second power signal (Ts) based on the at least one actual motor position and on a plurality (N) of predetermined motor positions, and applying the adjusted power signals (Us, Ts) to the wire interface (13).
